Creamy Lasagna Soup
  --Tieghan Gerard

1 lb spicy Italian chicken sausage
1/2 lb ground beef or chicken
1 yellow onion, chopped
3 tbsp Italian Seasoning
sea salt and pepper
28 oz can crushed tomatoes
1-2 c marinara sauce
4 c broth
4 c chopped baby spinach
1 lb mafaldine pasta, or 8 lasagna noodles
1 c heavy cream
1 c grated mozzarella or provolone
1/2 c grated parmesan
chopped basil or parsley, for serving

In a large Dutch oven, cook the sausage, beef, onions, and Italian seasonings until the meat is browned all over, 5-10 min. Add the crushed tomatoes, marinara sauce, and broth. Season with salt and pepper. Cook 10 min until thickened slightly. Stir in 2 c of water, and bring to a boil. Add the spinach and pasta, cooking until soft, ~10 min. Str in the cream, and both cheeses. Ladle the soup into bowls and serve topped with parmesan and fresh herbs. 
